#BANDERSNATCH on RASPBERRY PI
##Documentation

###Summary
This game is based on Bandersnatch, an interactive Netflix original movie. This is a decision-based text game with images to help visualization. 
This version of the game is meant to be played on Raspberry Pi and may not work with some environments.

###Dependencies
Follow the steps outlined in this guide for each of the dependencies:
http://lazyfoo.net/tutorials/SDL/01_hello_SDL/mac/index.php

SDL2: https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php
SDL2_image: https://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_image/
SDL2_TTF: https://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_ttf/

###BUILD
g++ -std=c++11 -o bandersnatch 02_getting_an_image_on_the_screen.cpp `sdl2-config --cflags --libs` -lSDL2_image -lSDL2_ttf

###DEPLOY
./bandersnatch

###USER INSTRUCTIONS
Click start on the initial page.
Use the left and right arrow keys to choose a decision when prompted.